Heron’s Gerald Ronson Begins Private Equity Group, FT Reports

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t
-- 
2011-04-11T00:49:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-11/heron-s-gerald-ronson-begins-private-equity-group-ft-reports.html
Heron International’s Gerald Ronson
created a private-equity group, Ronson Capital Partners, backed
by wealthy families, Middle Eastern sovereign wealth funds and
“like-minded partners,” the Financial Times reported, citing
RCP Chief Executive Officer Jonathan Goldstein.  The investment group, which has the capacity to invest more
than 500 million pounds ($818.2 million,) has made its first
purchase of an office tower in  London ’s West End and will focus
on investing in mainstream U.K. commercial property, the FT
said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blanche Gatt in London at 
